<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Test: Adjustments to fit content to page must obey guidelines (over-sized)</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Tom Clancy" href="mailto:tclancy@revenution.com"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#renderingpages"/>
  <meta name="flags" content="paged should" />
  <meta name="assert" content="If the specified page size is larger than the available media, the UA should scale the page down to fit the available media."/>
  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
   @page {
   	margin: 7%;
   	size:85in 110in;
	font-size: 2in;
	border: 1em solid green;
   }
   html, body {font-size: 2in;}
   div {
		margin-bottom: 2em;
   }
  ]]></style>
 </head>
 <body>
	<div>When printed, only letter-sized (8.5&quot;x11in) paper should be available. This page must have a green border around all 4 sides.</div>
	
	<div>The user agent may consult the user before printing.</div>
 </body>
</html>